# ⚕️ BMI & Health Tracker

A modern, cross-platform Body Mass Index (BMI) calculator and health tracking companion built with [Tauri v2](https://tauri.app/), [React](https://react.dev/), and [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/). It works seamlessly on Desktop (Windows) and Mobile (Android).

## ✨ Features

- **Personalized Health Profiles:** Create multiple user profiles. Set an avatar by picking an image or snapping a photo directly using the **in-app camera**.
- **Smart BMI Calculation:** Calculates exact BMI based on height, weight, age, and gender, providing a visual gauge.
- **Tailored Lifestyle Tips:** Don't just get a number! Get specific diet and exercise recommendations dynamically adjusted for children, teens, and adults.
- **Measurement History:** Keep a running log of your weight journey over time. Add **custom notes** to specific entries (e.g., "Post-holiday weigh-in").
- **PDF Report Exporting:** Generate and natively save clean, professional PDF reports of your health history directly to your device.
- **Daily Reminders:** Set up local, per-profile push notifications to remind you to log your weight or exercise.
- **Cross-Platform:** Employs Rust/Tauri to ensure incredible performance and tiny app sizes across Windows Executables and Android APKs.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack 

- **Frontend:** React.js, Vite, Tailwind CSS
- **Backend:** Rust, Tauri v2
- **Key Plugins Used:** 
  - `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` & `plugin-dialog` (Cross-platform file saving)
  - `@tauri-apps/plugin-notification` (Local push notifications)
  - WebRTC (`getUserMedia`) (Camera integration)

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
Make sure you have installed:
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (v20+)
- [Rust](https://www.rust-lang.org/)
- Android Studio / Android SDK (for mobile builds)

### Installation
1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/bmi-calculator.git
cd bmi-calculator
```

2. Install JavaScript dependencies:
```bash
npm install
```

### Running Locally

**For Desktop Preview:**
```bash
npx tauri dev
```

**For Android Preview (Emulator/Device):**
```bash
npx tauri android dev
```

## 📦 Building for Production

This project is configured with GitHub Actions to automate APK building, utilizing an optimized `[profile.release]` constraint to ensure small binary sizes. 

To build manually on your local machine:
```bash
# Build Android APK
npx tauri android build --apk --target aarch64

# Build Desktop Executable
npx tauri build
```
